Johnny, let’s keep it powerful but simple. Here’s a graduated law system that slots cleanly into the Immigration Office you’ve got without bloating the VM.

Core idea: 4 sanction tiers (one brain-cell to remember)

1. Notice — soft warning + education; no rights removed.


2. Probation — partial rights; rate‑limits & bond requirements.


3. Suspension — time‑boxed lockout (hours → days → weeks).


4. Revocation — Visa burned + Blacklist SBT (severe/recidivist).



This maps neatly to Misdemeanor vs Felony without building a full penal code.


---

Minimal legal vocabulary (fits in the VM)

OffenseClass: INFO, MISD_A, MISD_B, FELONY_C, FELONY_D
(Two misdemeanor bands, two felony bands = enough granularity.)

Sanction: { tier, duration, rights_mask, bond_delta, restitution_pct }

Rights mask (bitflags): GOVERN | WORK | TRADE | BUILD | OPERATE_ROBOT

Strike points: small integers that accumulate and decay over time.



---

Default sentencing policy (deterministic + tweakable)

INFO → Notice, 0 points, education link.

MISD_A (spam, emoji smuggling, mild policy bypass):

1st: Probation 7 days (limit GOVERN+BUILD), +bond 5%, 1 point

2nd: Suspension 24–72h, +bond 10%, 2 points


MISD_B (repeat abuse, mild fraud attempt):

1st: Suspension 7 days, +bond 15%, 3 points

2nd: Revocation (if ≥5 points total)


FELONY_C (theft, oracle tamper attempt, sybil orchestration):

Immediate Suspension 30 days, +bond 25%, 4 points

If prior points ≥3 → Revocation


FELONY_D (critical exploit, validator bribery, violent real‑world tie‑ins):

Immediate Revocation (+Blacklist), restitution required to appeal.



Point decay: −1 point every 30 days without offenses (never below 0).
Duration scaling: base_duration × (1 + 0.25 × prior_points) (capped).


---

Restorative first, punitive last

Restitution %: default 100% of verified harm routed by the Treasury Router.

Community service: protocol‑approved contributions (docs, tests, cleanup jobs) can offset suspension time (e.g., 1 accepted PR = −24h).

Education gate: short quiz / policy module completion required to exit Probation.



