enum OffenseClass { INFO, MISD_A, MISD_B, FELONY_C, FELONY_D }

struct SanctionState { tier, ends_at, rights_mask, points, bond_bp, restitution_bp }


Minimal new flows

sentence(holder, class, evidence_hash) → computes and applies SanctionState

current_rights(holder) → base Visa rights ∧ sanction rights mask

tick_decay(holder) → optional cron to decay points monthly

pay_restitution(holder, amount) → tracked toward appeals

complete_education(holder, module_id) → clears Probation faster


Permission check stays trivial

Existing is_permitted() becomes:

allowed = Visa.active && now < Visa.expiry
rights  = Permit.map(Visa.kind) AND Sanction.rights_mask
return allowed && rights includes requested

If tier == SUSPENSION → rights_mask = 0.
If tier == REVOCATION → unchanged (we already burn the Visa).


